FT  21 MAR 94 / Company News (This Week): RVI - Other companies
The trucks and buses arm of Renault, the French state-owned vehicle group,
will announce 1993 results tomorrow. The company, like all truck
manufacturers, is struggling to emerge from the sharp downturn in European
markets. The worst is now over, according to the company, and analysts are
expecting a substantial improvement on the losses of FFr1.6bn (Dollars 280m)
recorded in 1992.
